    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nnvim sets an incorrect file path when using `:cd` or `autochdir` to change the directory to file name containing double slashes. The file name is treated like the double slash is the beginning of the path: So `C:/code/proj/translation/input/en-ca//from-translator-2025-12-22.po` becomes `C:/from-translator-2025-12-22.po`.\n\nI would expect that it normalizes duplicated slashes into a single slash or maintains the double slash.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSimplest repro:\n```\n:edit C:/code/proj/translation/input/en-ca//from-translator-2025-12-22.po\n:echo expand(\"%:p\")\n:cd %:p:h\n:echo expand(\"%:p\")\n```\nOutput shows the path change:\n```\nC:/code/proj/translation/input/en-ca//from-translator-2025-12-22.po\nc:/from-translator-2025-12-22.po\n```\n\n----\n\nAlso occurs with `gf` and `autochdir` given c:/code/log.log file:\n```\nLoading PO file: C:/code/proj/translation/input/en-ca//from-translator-2025-12-22.po\n```\nC:/code/proj/translation/input/en-ca//from-translator-2025-12-22.po exists but can be empty.\n\n```\nnvim --clean +\"set autochdir\" c:/code/log.log\n/input<CR>gf\n:echo expand(\"%:p\")\n```\nOutput: `c:/from-translator-2025-12-22.po`\n\nYou can see that the path is incorrect. This mismatch causes lots of issues.\n\n(same result if `shellslash` is set.)\n\nAlso occurs in neovim 0.11.1.\n\nBoth of these setups work in vim:\n```\nvim -u DEFAULTS +\"set autochdir shellslash\" c:/code/log.log\nvim -u DEFAULTS +\"set autochdir\" c:/code/log.log\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWe should continue editing the same file. Possibly the file path should have normalized path names.\n\n`:echo expand(\"%:p\")` should output `C:/code/proj/translation/input/en-ca/from-translator-2025-12-22.po` and that should be the file we're editing.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.0.1576\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWin11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nCommand Prompt\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nnot set\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop",
