            "body": "Interesting case. Currently, when editing a file, if the parent directory exists, we canonicalize the path via `uv_fs_realpath`; otherwise, we leave it as-is. This means this issue can be reproduced even on Unix. e.g.\n```vim\n:e /private/tmp/real/target//a/b\n:cd /private/tmp/real/target\n```\n<img width=\"1354\" height=\"174\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a568257f-47ec-4e98-83c1-c7b85ce4a070\" />\n\nPossible solutions:\n1. Implement path canonicalization in nvim (e.g. removing redundant `/`, even `.` and `..`), but it might not be worth the effort. ðŸ¤”\n2. Change `path_shorten_fname` to skip consecutive `/`:\n    https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9492df027d0715e2bbd3508d6733fd6f6ca6de0b/src/nvim/path.c#L2124\n",
